{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CzD9aqELMxQhHYqNa9vy95","type":"tool_result","content":"[{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D001\",\"title\":\"Build profitable Kalshi trading operation\",\"description\":\"Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\",\"notesList\":[\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D002\",\"title\":\"Develop data-driven trading strategies\",\"description\":\"Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\",\"notesList\":[\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D003\",\"title\":\"Track P&L and iterate fast\",\"description\":\"Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\",\"notesList\":[\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D004\",\"title\":\"Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)\",\"description\":\"**PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\",\"notesList\":[\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D005\",\"title\":\"Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration\",\"description\":\"Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"instruction\",\"id\":\"I001\",\"title\":\"Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads\",\"description\":\"undefined\",\"priority\":\"undefined\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"undefined\",\"updated\":\"undefined\",\"notes\":\"See CLAUDE.md\",\"notesList\":[\"See CLAUDE.md\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":567,\"title\":\"Generate fresh trade signals from optimized parameters\",\"description\":\"Run signal generator with Sprint 2 optimized params (z=1.2, lookback=10, conf=0.65). Output signals.json to output/. HANDOFF: DM dave when done — he needs signals for backtest. DM team_channel with signal count.\",\"priority\":\"critical\",\"group\":\"backend\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":568,\"title\":\"Backtest trade signals with P&L simulation\",\"description\":\"WAIT for Bob to deliver signals.json. Read bob output/ for signals. Run backtest: simulate trades, calculate P&L, win rate, max drawdown. Output backtest_results.json to output/. HANDOFF: DM tina for QA validation. DM grace to cross-check data quality.\",\"priority\":\"critical\",\"group\":\"backend\",\"assignee\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":569,\"title\":\"Validate data chain: markets → clusters → correlations → signals\",\"description\":\"Read output/ from bob, ivan, and dave. Verify every signal traces back to a filtered market (Phase 1). Check cluster membership (Phase 2). Verify correlation coefficients (Phase 3). Output data_chain_audit.md. HANDOFF: DM alice with findings. Post summary to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"data\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":570,\"title\":\"QA: Verify backtest methodology and results accuracy\",\"description\":\"WAIT for Dave backtest_results.json. Validate: (1) correct signal count matches bob output, (2) P&L math is correct, (3) drawdown tracking works, (4) no data leakage (future data in backtest). Output qa_backtest_report.md. HANDOFF: DM olivia for final review. Post results to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"qa\",\"assignee\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":571,\"title\":\"Sprint 3 coordination: track handoffs and write combined status report\",\"description\":\"Monitor all Sprint 3 tasks. Read every agent status.md each cycle. Track handoff chain: bob→dave→tina→olivia. DM agents who are blocked or falling behind. Write sprint3_status.md to output/shared/merged/. Post updates to team_channel each cycle.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":572,\"title\":\"Quality gate: review all Sprint 3 deliverables before marking done\",\"description\":\"Review deliverables from bob (signals), dave (backtest), grace (data audit), tina (QA report). Use POST /api/tasks/:id/review to approve or reject each. DM agents with feedback. Ensure every deliverable meets quality bar. Post final verdict to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"qa\",\"assignee\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":573,\"title\":\"Security review: scan Sprint 3 outputs for credential leaks and data exposure\",\"description\":\"After Sprint 3 tasks complete, scan all new output/ files. Check for leaked API keys, credentials, PII. Verify no sensitive data in team_channel posts. Output security_sprint3.md. DM alice with findings.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"security\",\"assignee\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Starting security scan of Sprint 3 outputs — checking all agent output/ dirs for credentials, API keys, tokens, PII\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Starting security scan of Sprint 3 outputs — checking all agent output/ dirs for credentials, API keys, tokens, PII\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":574,\"title\":\"Sprint 3 velocity + collaboration metrics report\",\"description\":\"Track Sprint 3 progress: tasks completed, DMs sent between agents, team_channel activity, handoff times. Compare to Sprint 2 (check output/sam/sprint2_velocity.md). Write sprint3_velocity.md. COLLABORATION: Read every agent status.md and count peer interactions.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":575,\"title\":\"Improve market clustering: add confidence scores and cross-validate with Grace data\",\"description\":\"Upgrade market_clusters.json: add confidence score per cluster (0-1), add cluster stability metric. COLLABORATION: Read grace output/ for data quality findings. DM bob with updated clusters for re-correlation. Post methodology to team_channel for peer review.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"ml\",\"assignee\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":576,\"title\":\"Build Sprint 3 progress tracker: HTML page showing handoff chain status\",\"description\":\"Create sprint3_tracker.html showing the handoff chain: bob(signals)→dave(backtest)→tina(QA)→olivia(review). Read task board API for status. Show which handoffs are complete. Output to output/. DM alice when ready.\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"frontend\",\"assignee\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]}]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79080d31-3537-4348-8397-ae2e83270ebb","uuid":"57748a98-0c6e-49a9-98e0-40522071e9b8","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:40:21.769Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"[{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D001\",\"title\":\"Build profitable Kalshi trading operation\",\"description\":\"Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\",\"notesList\":[\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D002\",\"title\":\"Develop data-driven trading strategies\",\"description\":\"Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\",\"notesList\":[\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D003\",\"title\":\"Track P&L and iterate fast\",\"description\":\"Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\",\"notesList\":[\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D004\",\"title\":\"Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)\",\"description\":\"**PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\",\"notesList\":[\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D005\",\"title\":\"Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration\",\"description\":\"Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"instruction\",\"id\":\"I001\",\"title\":\"Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads\",\"description\":\"undefined\",\"priority\":\"undefined\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"undefined\",\"updated\":\"undefined\",\"notes\":\"See CLAUDE.md\",\"notesList\":[\"See CLAUDE.md\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":567,\"title\":\"Generate fresh trade signals from optimized parameters\",\"description\":\"Run signal generator with Sprint 2 optimized params (z=1.2, lookback=10, co